<div class="allianceSection collapsable collapsed">
	 <h4 class="header">Remarks</h4>
	<div class="text">  </div>
</div>

	
	
<div class="allianceSection collapsable collapsed">
	 <h4 class="header">Observations</h4>
	<div class="text"> Stands of <i>Spergularia marina</i> have been sampled at Humboldt Bay National Wildlife Refuge (263A) in seasonally flooded flats and newly scraped areas exposing mudflats of highly saline and acidic soils. It is likely an ephemeral, early seral vegetation type (Pickart 2006). We need more sampling and analysis to evaluate associations of this alliance and to understand relationships with similar alliances, including <i>Sesuvium verrucosum</i> alliance. The range of this alliance likely includes the Central California Coast (261A), Central California Coast Ranges (M262A), Great Valley (262A), Southern California Coast (261B), Southern California Mountains and Valleys (M262GB), Mojave Desert (322A), Sonoran Desert (322B), and Colorado Desert (322C) sections. </div>
</div>

	

    
